 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.30","title":"[AUDIT] Deep correctness audit: src/types/cancel.rs","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"RusticDune","created_at":"2026-02-16T15:11:24.878333307Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T15:15:44.140515292Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T15:15:44.140491287Z","close_reason":"Deep audit of src/types/cancel.rs (2189 lines). CLEAN — no fixes required. Pure data type module: CancelKind (11 variants), CancelPhase (4 variants), CancelWitness, CancelReason with cause chain, CancelAttributionConfig with depth/memory limits. No HashMap/HashSet, no unsafe, no panics, no atomics, no arithmetic overflow risks (uses saturating_sub). Strengthen operation is idempotent and associative (tested). Cleanup budgets scale correctly with severity. Minor test gap: CancelKind::LinkedExit missing from cleanup_budget_always_finite_and_positive test array (line 1378), but production code handles it correctly.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.30","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T15:11:24.878333307Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
