-- --nocapture PASS (35/35, exit=0); cargo check -p asupersync --lib PASS (exit=0). No residual local delta on this file after shared-branch advancement.","created_at":"2026-02-22T17:39:24Z"},{"id":1978,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Peer-review slice (commit c4339464): reviewed sqlite/snapshot/wheel/raptorq deltas; no functional regression reproduced. Added regression guards: time::wheel::tests::wheel_register_wraps_id_and_generation_without_immediate_collision and distributed::snapshot::tests::snapshot_huge_task_count_with_truncated_payload_returns_eof. rch validations: wheel test PASS (1/1, remote exit=0; local wrapper hit tail timeout after completion line), sqlite feature test PASS (1/1, exit=0), snapshot malformed-count test PASS (1/1, exit=0). rustfmt --check for touched files PASS.","created_at":"2026-02-22T17:58:51Z"},{"id":2009,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CopperHeron","text":"Takeover slice (CopperHeron, 2026-02-25): reviewed active changed surfaces in src/channel/mpsc.rs, src/runtime/scheduler/worker.rs, src/time/intrusive_wheel.rs plus related tests. No definitive behavioral regression confirmed in the reviewed diffs, but found semantic-documentation drift around Budget priority meet law (code uses min while docs/comments still stated max in several places). Patched docs/comments for semantic alignment in src/types/budget.rs and tests/algebraic_laws.rs commentary. Validation status: rch-offloaded targeted checks attempted; workspace currently has pre-existing compile blockers outside this review slice (e.g., src/grpc/codec.rs compressor ?-usage/type inference and src/combinator/pipeline.rs Cx::for_test symbol mismatch), which prevent full cargo test/check gates from going green in this branch state.","created_at":"2026-02-25T19:42:19Z"},{"id":2010,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CopperHeron","text":"Follow-up validation slice (2026-02-25): rch-offloaded cargo check --lib now passes (exit