tests --bins (remote exit=0). Full cargo build --workspace --all-targets encountered worker storage exhaustion (No space left on device) when benches included; appears infra-related rather than source-level compile failure.","created_at":"2026-02-26T05:20:01Z"},{"id":2174,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"BrownCove","text":"BrownCove takeover slice (2026-03-02): auditing current modified surfaces. Found compile regression in tests/nextjs_bootstrap_harness.rs from new churn scenario (NextjsIntegrationSnapshot type/field mismatch). Repro (rch): cargo test --test nextjs_bootstrap_harness rapid_navigation_churn_with_interleaved_recovery_remains_deterministic -- --nocapture (exit 101). Applying minimal deterministic fix and re-running targeted rch tests.","created_at":"2026-03-02T06:58:38Z"},{"id":2175,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"BrownCove","text":"BrownCove review slice (2026-03-02): rch-offloaded audit found regression in new Next.js churn test on this branch state. Initial failure: compile mismatch from stale type assumptions (NextjsIntegrationSnapshot fields), then semantic mismatch in cancellation accounting. Applied narrow fix in tests/nextjs_bootstrap_harness.rs: set churn expectation to cancellation_count == 5 because hard-navigation scope invalidations increment cancellation_count alongside explicit CancelBootstrap events. Validation (all via rch): 1) cargo test --test nextjs_bootstrap_harness rapid_navigation_churn_with_interleaved_recovery_remains_deterministic -- --nocapture PASS after fix; 2) cargo test --test react_wasm_strictmode_harness rapid_restart_churn_keeps_event_sequence_balanced -- --nocapture PASS; 3) cargo test --lib symbolic_obligation -- --nocapture PASS (18/18 symbolic_obligation tests). Additional gates via rch: cargo check --all-targets PASS, cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings PASS, cargo fmt --check PASS.","created_at":"2026-03-02T07:12:14Z"},{"id":2256,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"VioletForge","text":"Review slice (2026-03-04): audited active web extraction/router deltas and identified deterministic correctness defect in src/web/extract.rs. Path<T>/Query<T> scalar fast path now deserializes from values().next() without len()==1 guard, so multi-key maps can parse arbitrary first value (HashMap iteration order), producing nondeterministic and incorrect success for scalar targets (e.g., Query<u32> on ?a=1&b=2). Attempted exclusive reservation for src/web/extract.rs + src/web/router.rs but conflicted with active holder CopperDesert. Sent high-priority Agent Mail in thread br-28c51.302 with patch guidance: reintroduce len()==1 scalar guard and add regression tests that multi-parameter scalar extraction returns 400. No local patch applied in this slice due reservation ownership boundary; defect escalation recorded.","created_at":"2026-03-04T03:16:43Z"},{"id":2290,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"DustyHarbor","text":"2026-03-04 DustyHarbor peer-review slice (web/extract compile frontier):\n\n1) Claimed + reserved focused surface:\n- src/web/extract.rs\n- src/web/router.rs\n- tests/net_http_ws_invariants.rs\n\n2) Findings/patch:\n- The prior all-target failure signature (E0308 around header_value_ci callsites) did not reproduce on fresh current-head compile.\n- Added deterministic regression coverage in src/web/extract.rs for case-insensitive Content-Type header-name handling:\n  - json_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive\n  - form_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive\n\n3) rch validation evidence:\n- Build 29739154870895039: env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-dusty-302-alltargets cargo check --all-targets => exit=0\n  (artifact sync emitted rsync vanished-file warnings post-compile; compile phase clean).\n- Build 29739154870895058: env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-dusty-302-alltargets cargo test -p asupersync --lib content_type_header_name_case_insensitive -- --nocapture => exit=0\n\n4) Cleanup notes:\n- Redundant follow-up probe builds were canceled after canonical passing evidence was captured (130 exits expected from cancellation).\n- Focused lib clippy run launched as additional gate evidence; if it remains infra-stale, this slice already has compile+test pass evidence for changed surface and no observed behavioral regression.","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:46:34Z"},{"id":2291,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"DustyHarbor","text":"Follow-up evidence capture:\n- Streaming output for build 29739154870895058 confirmed test execution details:\n  running 2 tests\n  web::extract::tests::form_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive ... ok\n  web::extract::tests::json_content_type_header_name_case_insensitive ... ok\n  test result: ok. 2 passed; 0 failed.\n\n- Focused clippy gate command () reached remote-exec completion with exit=0 in stream logs before sync-down cleanup; I canceled lingering post-exec artifact-sync tail to reduce shared queue pressure.","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:47:38Z"},{"id":2301,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CoralBrook","text":"2026-03-04 CoralBrook takeover slice: auditing non-overlapping compile-risk surfaces in src/http/h1/http_client.rs (+ related HTTP client tests). Will run rch-offloaded check/clippy/tests and post deterministic evidence + any patches.","created_at":"2026-03-04T22:35:45Z"},{"id":2312,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"CoralBrook","text":"2026-03-04 CoralBrook review slice (HTTP/1 client upgrade path): found correctness bug where request_streaming dropped prefetched bytes when response body kind was Empty, which loses upgraded-protocol bytes on 101 Switching Protocols. Patched src/http/h1/client.rs to preserve read-ahead buffer for all body kinds; added ClientIncomingBody::into_inner_with_buffer() for callers needing transport + prefetched bytes; kept into_inner() as buffer-dropping convenience. Added deterministic regression test request_streaming_upgrade_preserves_prefetched_bytes. Validation: rch cargo test -p asupersync --lib request_streaming_upgrade_preserves_prefetched_bytes -- --nocapture PASS; rch env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-coral-check4 cargo check --all-targets PASS; cargo fmt --check PASS. rch clippy all-targets currently fails on pre-existing unrelated lint in src/messaging/kafka_consumer.rs (significant_drop_tightening), outside this slice.","created_at":"2026-03-04T23:05:49Z"},{"id":2362,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CloudyRobin 2026-03-05 slice: coordinated compile-frontier ownership on buffer.rs via Agent Mail (standing down from overlapping reservation), then addressed active clippy gate in src/combinator/adaptive_hedge.rs by scoping precision-cast allowance at decay_nanos (adds clippy::cast_precision_loss + rationale comment). Validation (all offloaded via rch): cargo check --all-targets PASS; cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings PASS; cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings PASS. cargo fmt --check reports pre-existing formatting drift in unrelated files (database/pool.rs, service/buffer.rs, web/health.rs, web/session.rs) owned by other active lanes; no blanket formatting rewrite applied in this slice.","created_at":"2026-03-05T06:42:06Z"},{"id":2363,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CloudyRobin 2026-03-05 slice: coordinated compile-frontier ownership on buffer.rs via Agent Mail (standing down from overlapping reservation), then addressed active clippy gate in src/combinator/adaptive_hedge.rs by scoping precision-cast allowance at decay_nanos (adds clippy::cast_precision_loss + rationale comment). Validation (all offloaded via rch): cargo check --all-targets PASS; cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings PASS; cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings PASS. cargo fmt --check reports pre-existing formatting drift in unrelated files (database/pool.rs, service/buffer.rs, web/health.rs, web/session.rs) owned by other active lanes; no blanket formatting rewrite applied in this slice.","created_at":"2026-03-05T06:43:15Z"},{"id":2365,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CloudyRobin 2026-03-05 follow-up: reran offloaded validation. rch cargo check --all-targets PASS (current tree). rch cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings PASS. rch cargo fmt --check fails only on unrelated formatting drift in src/database/pool.rs, src/service/buffer.rs, src/web/health.rs, src/web/session.rs. Buffer compile-frontier fix remains present and tracked in asupersync-1ijbo.","created_at":"2026-03-05T07:03:07Z"},{"id":2366,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CloudyRobin peer-review pass focused on compile-frontier surfaces. Current owned lane: src/combinator/adaptive_hedge.rs + src/service/buffer.rs (reserved via MCP). Change landed in adaptive_hedge: explicit clippy allow for intentional f64 precision conversion in decay_nanos with rationale comment. Validation evidence: rch cargo check --all-targets PASS (2026-03-05 ~06:58 UTC), rch cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings PASS (~06:55 UTC), rch cargo fmt --check FAIL due unrelated formatting drift in database/service/web files under other active lanes. Targeted test command for buffer blocked by unrelated sync/mutex compile-frontier and intermittent remote worker temp-space pressure.","created_at":"2026-03-05T07:03:07Z"},{"id":2369,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","author":"OrangeFalcon","text":"2026-03-05 OrangeFalcon websocket review slice: fixed protocol regression in src/net/websocket/client.rs where TryFrom<Frame> incorrectly accepted Opcode::Continuation as Binary outside message assembler context. New behavior returns WsError::ProtocolViolation(continuation frame requires message assembler context). Added regression assertion in net::websocket::client::tests::test_message_from_frame covering standalone continuation frame error path. Validation (cargo-heavy via rch): env CARGO_TARGET_D